news.title: Finance ministry tightens definition of beneficial owners under PMLA
news.para: Under the anti-money laundering law, 'reporting entities' are banks and financial institutions, firms engaged in real estate and jewellery sectors. They also include intermediaries in casinos and crypto or virtual digital assets.

news.title: Cidco's Rs 699 crore spend on consultants questioned
news.para: Cidco has awarded the contract collectively worth over Rs 699 crore to provide marketing, branding, sales and post-sales services for its 67,000 residential and commercial units developed under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojna (PMAY) project.

news.title: Maharashtra budget: Housing scheme named after PM; 10 lakh units planned
news.para: Fadnavis reiterated the government's commitment to the Prime Minister's Housing for All, 2022, scheme announcing a programme for construction of 10 lakh houses in rural areas.

news.title: Jaypee insolvency: YEIDA to move NCLAT, says won't forgo Rs 1,600 crore extra compensation
news.para: YEIDA chief executive officer Arun Vir Singh held talks with the Mumbai-based asset reconstruction company's managing director and CEO Aalok Dave.

news.title: RateGain's founder buys bungalow in Delhi's Golf Links for Rs 127.5 crore
news.para: According to registry documents accessed by Zapkey, the property was registered on February 24 in the names of Bhanu Chopra and Megha Chopra, and they paid Rs 6.79 crore in stamp duty to Rategain founder Bhanu Chopra for the transaction.

news.title: Bessemer India Capital exits Home First Finance, sells 7.75% stake for Rs 467 crore
news.para: Fidelity Funds - Asian Smaller Companies Pool and Nomura Trust and Banking Co. Ltd bought a total of 11.93 lakh equity shares of the company.

news.title: Picard Angst India buys land, bungalow in Mumbai for Rs 86.52 crore
news.para: The company has purchased the property from five joint owners, including global banking and finance professional Francis Andrew Rozario, former CEO & executive director at Temasek’s Fullerton Financial Holdings (International).

news.title: Suraksha group to infuse Rs 250 crore, arrange Rs 3,000 crore loan to complete 20,000 Jaypee flats
news.para: ​As per the resolution plan of Suraksha Group submitted in June 2021, Jaypee Infratech Ltd (JIL) will get delisted and public shareholders will be given an aggregate exit at a price of Rs 0.14 crore.

news.title: Irish banks see commercial real estate revaluations as manageable
news.para: A shift to home working has put pressure on the Irish office market, which experienced a boom in recent years thanks largely to high levels of investment from multinational tech firms, some of whom are now cutting back on their hiring sprees, including letting people go.

news.title: Boston council passes proposal aimed at tackling rising rent
news.para: Under Mayor Michelle Wu's proposal, known as a home rule petition, the maximum allowable annual rent increase would be based on the change in the consumer price index, plus 6%, or a maximum increase of 10% - whichever is lower.

news.title: China Evergrande chairman's seized Hong Kong mansion put up for sale
news.para: The mansion, located in the prestigious The Peak residential district, could be the first known case of chairman Hui Ka Yan's personal assets in Hong Kong being seized.

news.title: MahaRERA scam: Two architects who prepared plan layouts of buildings untraceable
news.para: The ED is independently investigating MahaRERA scam suspecting the developers used black money to construct these buildings illegally, made revenue loss of state government and had obtained all fraud-related documents from concerned departments like KDMC as well as MahaRERA office.

news.title: Two metro corridors to open next year in Mumbai region, another five by 2025
news.para: Nearly 185km length of Metro works are being undertaken in MMR, of which 32.5 km (Colaba-Bandra-Seepz) Metro 3 underground corridor is executed by Mumbai Metro Rail Corporation (MMRC) and the remaining by Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority (MMRDA).

news.title: Why Manesar civic body doesn't want to take over upkeep of streetlights in new sectors
news.para: Lack of illumination on arterial roads has been a major cause of concern for residents living in sectors 81-95, who have been frequently complaining about poorly lit stretches posing a risk of accidents and security concerns.

news.title: Sebi extends deadline till Mar 15 to submit public comments on proposal on REITs, InvITs sponsors
news.para: ​​The regulator had put in place a consultation paper on holding of sponsors in Real Estate Investment Trust (REITs) and Infrastructure Investment Trust (InvITs) on February 23 and sought public comments on the same by March 8.
